{"questionId":"20618","questionHtml":"<p>Which monomer forms the polymer shown?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a5c1b71c7b8935a78ab6e6ce1eb4f02b08bcddd9.png\"></p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>CH(Cl)=CH(CH</mtext><mtext>3</mtext></msub><mtext>)</mtext></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>CH</mtext><mtext>2</mtext></msub><msub><mtext>=C(Cl)CH</mtext><mtext>3</mtext></msub></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>(CH</mtext><mtext>3</mtext></msub><msub><mtext>)</mtext><mtext>2</mtext></msub><mtext>CHCl</mtext></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>CH</mtext><mtext>2</mtext></msub><mtext>=CHCl</mtext></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"20618","referenceCode":"21M.1.sl.TZ2.26","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which monomer forms the polymer shown? A. CH(Cl)=CH(CH3) B. CH2=C(Cl)CH3 C. (CH3)2CHCl D. CH2=CHCl","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}